quran[22]{c,v,t}:
  85,1,"(I swear) by the sky, with (all) its constellations"
  85,2,(And by) the promised day (of Judgment)
  85,3,"And (by) the witness (bearing the evidence), as well as the evidence (itself)"
  85,4,Doomed are the people of the ditch
  85,5,(The ditch) full of fire and abundant fuel
  85,6,"Remember, when the unbelievers sat by the fire"
  85,7,And were themselves witness to what they did to the believers
  85,8,"They were hostile (and rancorous), just because the believers believed in Allah, the most Powerful and the most Praiseworthy"
  85,9,To Whom belongs the Kingdom of the heavens and the earth. Allah is the Witness to every single thing
  85,10,"Indeed, those who persecuted the believing men and women and then failed to repent, would (certainly) face the torture of hell. For them, is the punishment of the blazing fire"
  85,11,While the (blissful) paradise _ rivers run right through it _ is for those who believe and do righteous deeds. That is the greatest triumph
  85,12,"Your Lord´s punishment is very severe, indeed"
  85,13,"It is He Who created; and He it is, Who will recreate"
  85,14,He is the most Forgiving and the most Loving
  85,15,Owner of the majestic throne
  85,16,(The Efficient Achiever)! He does what He pleases
  85,17,Has the story of the armies reached you
  85,18,(Armies of) the pharaoh and the (people of) ´Samood´
  85,19,"The unbelievers, in fact (were and) are (persistent) in their denial"
  85,20,Allah has surrounded them all around
  85,21,This (narrative) is certainly the majestic Qur´an
  85,22,Safely preserved on (the sacred) slates